name: Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc.
category: Fraternity & Sorority Life - SI RSO Fraternity & Sorority Life
mission: Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated was founded on January 13, 1913, by 22 collegiate women at Howard University to promote academic excellence and provide assistance to those in need. The Founders of Delta Sigma Theta envisioned an organization committed to sisterhood, scholarship, service, and addressing the social issues of the time. Since its founding, Delta Sigma Theta has become one of the preeminent service-based sororities, with more than 350,000 initiated members and over 1,050 chartered chapters worldwide. As a sisterhood comprised primarily of Black, college-educated women, the Sorority seriously considers the issues impacting the Black community and boldly confronts the challenges of African Americans and, hence, all Americans. Over the years, a wide range of programs addressing education, health, international development, and the strengthening of African American families have evolved. The major programs of the Sorority are based upon the Five-Point Programmatic Thrust: economic development, educational development, international awareness and involvement, physical and mental health, and political awareness and involvement.

mission: The Pacific Islander Student Association (PISA) at San José State University is dedicated to fostering a vibrant, inclusive, and empowering community for students of Pacific Islander heritage and allies. These experiences help you build essential skills in communication, teamwork, and organization.The association also supports your academic and career growth. Members have access to mentorship, scholarship resources, tutoring, internship leads, and resume workshops to help you achieve your goals. PISA also connects you with campus departments, alumni, and community leaders to expand your professional network and increase representation for Pacific Islander students in higher education.Membership includes invitations to exclusive events such as socials, retreats, game nights, and cultural trips. Members enjoy early registration and reduced prices for special programs. You will also receive PISA merchandise like t-shirts and hoodies to proudly represent our community on and off campus.Being part of PISA is more than joining a student organization. It is an opportunity to grow as a leader, embrace your identity, and create lasting impact while surrounded by a community that celebrates you every step of the way.

We also empower young activists to get involved in the fight for free markets and limited government. Through building strong campus networks, organizing conferences, and equipping activists with the knowledge and strategies needed to combat the left, TPUSA empowers young people to make a difference within their community. This club also helps students register to vote. TPUSA has helped thousands of college students apply for voter registration and access absentee ballots.
benefits: This club provides a safe space to discuss difficult topics that are often hard to talk about. This club also provides a place to socialize with people who are like minded and understanding.

name: UNITE
category: Recognized Student Organization - SI RSO Special Interest
mission: The mission of the organization is to foster student leadership, advocate for equitable education, and create a support network for undocumented and mixed-status students within the academic community. Through a combination of education, advocacy, and collaboration, the organization aims to build bridges and create an inclusive community that empowers students and their families. The organization also seeks to raise awareness about the unique challenges faced by vulnerable immigrant communities by amplifying diverse voices and experiences. Furthermore, the commitment extends to increasing campus opportunities for undocumented and mixed-status students to support their academic and career goals. Overall, the mission is to create a more inclusive and supportive academic environment for all students, fostering an atmosphere of understanding, empathy, and shared growth

name: Veterans Student Organization
category: Recognized Student Organization - SI RSO Academic
mission: We are a service and support group at San Jose State University which is located in the Silicon Valley. Our mission is to bring past, present, and future members of the Armed Forces together to promote, unify and support the military veteran voice on and off campus. Our aims are to educate the campus and local community about how the military has affected our lives and to support one another through the transition process of reintegration. Our goals are to promote, support, unify, motivate and provide camaraderie to our veteran brothers and sisters in arms. We welcome any interested SJSU students to learn firsthand the ways of the warrior culture. Lastly, we offer our family of Spartan Warriors a meeting place for Veteran Affairs matters which include military benefits, readjustment services, and links to external U.S. government organizations.

name: Vietnamese Student Association

mission: The purpose of the Vietnamese Student Association at SJSU is to serve the Vietnamese community by preserving and sharing Vietnamese culture and traditions. We aim to keep our culture alive for those born or raised outside of Vietnam and welcome people of all backgrounds who want to learn. We work together to create a supportive environment that encourages education, leadership, and teamwork.
benefits: Members will be able to engage in cultural enrichment and join a thriving community of people, ready to welcome others with open arms. Members will also have the opportunity to further develop their leadership and professional skills through various committees that we offer. Members will have exclusive access to attend and participate in several of our cultural events throughout the year.

name: Women in Animation Student Chapter at San Jose State University
category: Recognized Student Organization - SI RSO Academic
mission: Women In Animation is dedicated to advancing underrepresented genders in the field of animation. As an organization, we envision a world where underrepresented genders share equally in the creation, production and rewards of animation in all industries including visual effects, feature length animation, TV programming, Gaming, VR and AR, and we provide resources and connections to make it happen. With every event we plan, we aim to provide or instill resources to achieve equity goals in the industry, empower and advocate for underrepresented gender identities, bring together our local community, and provide tools for professional development.
benefits: Members of our club get to belong to a fun and creative community that celebrates diversity in every field of the animation industry. WIA at SJSU is great for making new friends, professional connections, learning new skills and hearing from industry professionals. WIA at SJSU is completely free to join and we love to collaborate with other clubs to increase connection and learning from other facets of the animation industry.
